  <revision rev="10" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>a5744af77d6fa24edf440a3031b8b8f9</srcmd5>
    <version>0.370.0</version>
    <time>1781191798</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- updated to 0.370.0 (0.37)
   see /usr/share/doc/packages/perl-File-MimeInfo/Changes
  0.37  2026-05-19
   - Honor XDG_DATA_HOME precedence for extension globs, so a glob entry
     from a higher-priority data dir overrides one from a lower-priority
     dir instead of being silently shadowed (#62, liujianqiang-niu).
   - Fix open() precedence and stale filehandle bugs in
     File::MimeInfo::default and File::MimeInfo::Magic.
   - Don't die when @ARGV contains bytes that are invalid in the current
     locale; decode leniently and continue.
   - Refactor resolvelink to use Cwd::abs_path instead of a hand-rolled
     loop.
   - mimetype/mimeopen: quote filenames in diagnostic output via
     B::cstring so unusual characters render unambiguously.
  0.36  2026-01-11
   - Move to Codeberg</comment>
    <requestid>1358719</requestid>
  </revision>
</revisionlist>
